<font face="trebuchet ms" size="3">The 1965 Royal Commission on Local Government (The Redcliffe-Maude Commission) recommended that local			councils should be empowered to do what they pleased for the benefit of their people, and a consequence			of this was the very important 1972 Local Government Act which removed many of the restrictions on the			activities of parish councils. For example, before the 1972 Act, parish councils couldn’t save money 			from one year to the next in order to fund a major project.</font><br>
</div>
